body:

Here are some of the static website management systems I considered for this site

Thanks to @Netlify's https://www.staticgen.com/ 

### Lektor
https://www.getlektor.com 
Worked on mac & Raspberry Pi

### Tinkerer
http://tinkerer.me/pages/documentation.html
* Got an error after install: `Could not import extension tinkerer.ext.blog (exception: No module named compat)`
	
### Statik
https://github.com/thanethomson/statik/wiki/Installation
* Got an error after install : `No handlers could be found for logger "statik.cmdline"`

### Various
Didn't review these ones yet
+ http://tarbell.readthedocs.io/en/1.0.5/tutorial.html    interesting, leverages google spreadsheets for content, has interesting map builder backed by google docs for the coords.
+ https://grow.io/start/       has a CMS ??
+ http://hyde.github.io
+ http://www.mkdocs.org                  focused on  documentation generation
+ https://www.getnikola.com
+ https://posativ.org/acrylamid/
+ http://blogofile.com
+ http://urubu.jandecaluwe.com/start.html
+ https://pythonhosted.org/Frozen-Flask/		staticifies a Flask web dev 
+ http://www.sphinx-doc.org/en/master/tutorial.html	focused on  documentation generation
+ http://staticjinja.readthedocs.io/en/latest/
+ https://github.com/kingcons/coleslaw             lisp based


